# Core Concepts

## Project Structure

```sh
app/
├── components/                         # Shared UI components
├── features/                           # Feature-specific code
│   ├── _shared/                        # Shared features
│   │   └── shared-feature-name/
│   │       ├── api/                    # API layer
│   │       ├── domain/                 # Business logic
│   │       ├── emails/                 # Email templates
│   │       └── ui/                     # UI components
│   └── feature-name/
│       ├── api/                        # API layer
│       ├── domain/                     # Business logic
│       ├── ui/                         # UI components
│       └── tests/                      # Feature tests
├── drizzle/                           # Database schemas
│   └── schema/                         # Table definitions
├── lib/                               # Core utilities
│   ├── client/                         # Client-side core
│   ├── server/                         # Server-side core
│   └── shared/                         # Isomorphic utilities
├── providers/                         # Shared Providers
├── routes/                            # Route components
└── styles/                            # Global styles
```

## Technology Stack

### Core Technologies

- React 19 for UI
- TypeScript for type safety
- TanStack Router for routing
- TanStack Query for data fetching
- TanStack Start for server functions
- Drizzle for database operations

### UI Layer

- Shadcn UI for components
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Radix UI for primitives

### Data Layer

- PostgreSQL for database
- Drizzle ORM for queries
- Zod for validation

## File Organization

### Naming Conventions

- Components: `component-name.tsx`
- API Layer: `feature-name.api.ts`
- Forms: `feature-name.form.tsx`
- Database: `table-name.schema.ts`
- Tests: `feature-name.test.ts`

### Directory Structure

- Use lowercase with dashes
- Group by feature first
- Keep related files close
- Follow consistent patterns

## Development Workflow

### Code Style

- Use ESLint for linting
- Follow commit conventions
- Write meaningful tests
- Document complex logic

### Best Practices

- Follow layer-specific guidelines:
  - [API Layer](mdc:.cursor/rules/api.mdc)
  - [Client Layer](mdc:.cursor/rules/client.mdc)
  - [Data Layer](mdc:.cursor/rules/data.mdc)

### Testing Strategy

- Unit tests with Vitest
- Component tests with RTL
- Integration tests for flows
- E2E tests for critical paths

### Documentation

- Use JSDoc for functions
- Document API endpoints
- Keep README files updated
- Include setup instructions
